Host-gated pod reconnection and lean pod pushes

Maintain one reconnection loop per host instead of one per pod, and
push from pods only when local refs show the gateway is behind.

Host connections now publish liveness on a watch channel and own a
single background monitor (SSH gains one, matching Kubernetes). Pod
event loops wait on that watch before touching the pod endpoint rather
than each probing the host, so N pods on one host share one retry loop
and a pod connection is always gated on host reachability.

The pod /events handler no longer force-pushes on every connection. It
compares each branch to its rumpelpod remote-tracking ref and pushes,
asynchronously, only when the gateway is behind, so enter and claude do
no unnecessary git work on connect.
